<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 9000 Pro Sleeper After 05/01/1997, and 9800 Model After 07/01/1997 -
        REMOVE AND INSTALL - CAB BLEND-DOOR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>CAB BLEND-DOOR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcsubproc id="hl1602012">
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch and A/C switch are in the OFF position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the passenger seat and Blend-Air unit cover. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_17.xml" xrefid="hl1602007">BLEND-AIR UNIT COVER, Remove</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two clips: one securing the cab blend-door assembly to the evaporator (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602048">Figure 29</hotlnk>), and one securing the cab blend-door assembly to the
                    bunk blend-door assembly (
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_21.xml" xrefid="f1602052">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1602048" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/g1602048.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 29. Clip Securing Cab Blend-Door Assembly to Evaporator</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the clip that secures the HOT-COLD cable in position on the cab Blend-Air door (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602020">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the hold down clamp for the HOT-COLD cable and remove the cable from the
                    blend-door (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602020">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the five nuts that secure the cab blend-door assembly to the bottom of the
                    Blend-Air unit and lift the cab blend-door assembly straight up and out of the Blend-Air unit (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602050">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1602020" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figG16/G1602018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                             scalefitheight="432px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 30. Connection of HOT-COLD Cable to Cab Blend-Door Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1602050" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/g1602020A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 31. Cab Blend-Door Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="hl1602013">
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the cab blend-door assembly into the Blend-Air unit (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602050">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the five nuts that secure the cab blend-door assembly to the bottom of the
                    Blend-Air unit. Tighten to 13 lbf-in (1.46 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the two clips securing the cab blend-door assembly to the evaporator and the
                    bunk blend-door assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602048">Figure 29</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_21.xml" xrefid="f1602052">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the HOT-COLD cable to the blend-door and secure in place with the clip (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602020">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the clamp to secure the HOT-COLD cable in place (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602020">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>In the following step, to verify correct operation at the air duct outlets, the cover must be
                        in place on the Blend-Air unit.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Test operation.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install Blend-Air unit cover and passenger seat. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_17.xml" xrefid="hl1602006">BLEND-AIR UNIT COVER, Install</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
